---
title: Szechuan Beef & Green Beans with Ginger Rice & Candied Peanuts
description: Put down that delivery menu! This spicy-sweet stir-fry (say that 5 times fast) has got you covered. You’ll toss beef and green beans in an addictive Szechuan sauce that’s got just the right level of heat. Everything’s served over steamy, ginger-infused rice, then topped with crunchy candied peanuts. Plus, it’s all ready in just 30 minutes—take that, takeout!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/60eeeef0372f980b1f23b918-4e7afa1b.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/szechuan-beef-green-beans-60eeeef0372f980b1f23b918-40bbb05b.pdf
course: main course
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/szechuan-beef-green-beans-60eeeef0372f980b1f23b918
cuisine: Asian
nutrition:
  calories: 910 kcal
  fat: 42 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 99 g
  sugar: 26 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 2660 mg
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim green beans if
necessary; cut @green beans{6%ounce} crosswise into 2-inch pieces. Trim and thinly
slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #small pot{} over medium-high
heat. Add half the ginger; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups water for 4), and a big
pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until
rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, place green beans in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}. Add a splash of
water, then cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.
Uncover, drain, and set aside.

Heat a large, preferably #nonstick pan{}, over medium-high heat. Add
@peanuts{1%ounce}, @sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings), and 2 TBSP water. Cook,
stirring, until water has evaporated and peanuts are coated and lightly toasted,
~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wash out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in pan used for peanuts over
medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces,
until browned, ~{4-6%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Stir green beans, scallion whites, remaining ginger, and @sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4
servings) into pan with beef. Cook, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan,
until ginger is fragrant, ~{1%minute}.
> TIP: If ginger and scallion whites begin to brown too quickly, reduce heat to
medium low.

Stir in @Szechuan paste{2%tablespoon}, @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, and ¼ cup
water (1⁄3 cup for 4). Cook, stirring, until beef is cooked through and everything
is thoroughly coated in sauce, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; season with salt and @pepper{}. Taste Szechuan beef and
green beans and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with beef mixture. Sprinkle with scallion
greens and peanuts. Serve.